that wasn't meant to be done.

545
00:31:43,036 --> 00:31:45,073
Everybody's got to die sometime.

546
00:31:50,857 --> 00:31:52,330
<i>Memento mori.</i>

547
00:31:52,812 --> 00:31:54,666
Anybody here know what that means?

548
00:31:56,100 --> 00:31:58,770
It means "remember, you're gonna die."

549
00:32:00,840 --> 00:32:03,883
The roman slaves used to say it...
<i>Memento mori.</i>

550
00:32:05,559 --> 00:32:06,636
Remember it,

551
00:32:07,313 --> 00:32:09,973
or you're gonna live your life
like a dumb animal.

552
00:32:13,252 --> 00:32:15,850
Maybe y'all need to read a book
every now and then.

553
00:32:45,244 --> 00:32:47,333
You can take your shot at me now.

554
00:32:49,141 --> 00:32:50,196
Go ahead.

555
00:32:51,746 --> 00:32:52,970
It's the code.

556
00:32:59,981 --> 00:33:01,649
I know you had to do that

557
00:33:01,809 --> 00:33:04,277
on account of what I did
to your daddy and all.

558
00:33:05,213 --> 00:33:06,863
I got no hard feelings.

559
00:33:11,561 --> 00:33:15,149
It would be common courtesy
for somebody to help me to my feet.

560
00:33:15,683 --> 00:33:16,956
Right about now, huh?

561
00:33:20,351 --> 00:33:21,210
Good lads.

562
00:33:33,451 --> 00:33:36,225
Somebody get me something to drink,
for Christ sakes.

563
00:33:37,761 --> 00:33:39,771
Whatever happened to irish hospitality?

564
00:33:51,746 --> 00:33:52,576
What?

565
00:33:52,696 --> 00:33:54,202
I'm scared all the time.

566
00:33:55,854 --> 00:33:57,218
Of what, darling?

567
00:33:57,532 --> 00:33:59,832
Feeling something bad's gonna happen.

568
00:34:02,419 --> 00:34:05,219
Things I should have done, I didn't do.

569
00:34:08,133 --> 00:34:10,468
And now I'm living
in this kind of purgatory.

570
00:34:11,688 --> 00:34:13,883
That's life in Edenfalls, honey.

571
00:34:14,853 --> 00:34:16,265
That's life everywhere.

572
00:34:18,182 --> 00:34:19,729
You know what you need?

573
00:34:22,507 --> 00:34:25,525
I promised Wayne
I wouldn't do that no more.

574
00:34:26,010 --> 00:34:28,135
I'm not talking about drugs, honey.

575
00:34:31,043 --> 00:34:33,350
All I'm saying is you need to...

576
00:34:34,152 --> 00:34:36,828
figure out what it is
that you're afraid of.

577
00:34:39,159 --> 00:34:40,415
What are you afraid of?

578
00:34:41,823 --> 00:34:43,399
Being alone, mostly.

579
00:34:47,047 --> 00:34:49,227
Nobody to be loving me anymore,

580
00:34:50,184 --> 00:34:52,266
Ntaking care of me anymore.

581
00:34:54,357 --> 00:34:55,763
I love you, Nina.

582
00:34:56,410 --> 00:34:57,605
I love you, too.

583
00:34:59,590 --> 00:35:01,604
Now, come on, stop it.

584
00:35:01,846 --> 00:35:03,813
Let's go get us some good shit.

585
00:35:07,301 --> 00:35:08,131
What?

586
00:35:09,635 --> 00:35:12,551
Nina, you're meeting
your dealer at church?

587
00:35:13,983 --> 00:35:16,367
Of course not. It's an A.A. meeting.

588
00:35:35,294 --> 00:35:36,124
What?

589
00:35:40,993 --> 00:35:43,478
No, no, I'm coming right over.

590
00:35:44,140 --> 00:35:47,826
I started using, drinking
around sixth grade.

591
00:35:50,092 --> 00:35:52,068
I dropped out at 10th grade

592
00:35:52,188 --> 00:35:54,692
and started hitchhiking
across the country.

593
00:35:55,358 --> 00:35:57,143
Lost touch with my family.

594
00:35:59,246 --> 00:36:00,540
By the '80s,

595
00:36:00,794 --> 00:36:03,945
I was slamming meth
and robbing people as a way of life.

596
00:36:05,576 --> 00:36:09,171
I ate out of trash cans,
slept in abandoned houses,

597
00:36:09,955 --> 00:36:12,172
until my arrest record
caught up with me,

598
00:36:12,503 --> 00:36:14,255
and I wound up behind bars.

599
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:16,839
After I did some time,

600
00:36:17,205 --> 00:36:19,114
I got my shit together.

601
00:36:19,234 --> 00:36:21,242
I cleaned up my prison record,

602
00:36:21,524 --> 00:36:23,507
got a whole new life for myself.

603
00:36:25,107 --> 00:36:27,021
It was my 30th birthday.

604
00:36:27,530 --> 00:36:31,400
I figured, things were going so well,
why shouldn't I be able to celebrate?

605
00:36:32,853 --> 00:36:34,350
Two days later,

606
00:36:34,851 --> 00:36:36,761
I woke up in a motel,

607
00:36:37,824 --> 00:36:40,862
naked, sweating, shivering cold.

608
00:36:41,717 --> 00:36:44,235
There I was on parole,

609
00:36:44,750 --> 00:36:46,350
my life hanging by a thread,

610
00:36:46,470 --> 00:36:48,918
and I had relapsed,
and I didn't even know why.

611
00:36:50,242 --> 00:36:52,004
I had a shotgun at the house,

612
00:36:53,281 --> 00:36:56,425
and I thought
I'd put the barrel in my mouth

613
00:36:56,586 --> 00:36:58,048
and pull the trigger.

614
00:36:59,286 --> 00:37:01,706
That way, I'd finally get some peace.

615
00:37:05,646 --> 00:37:06,631
That's it.

616
00:37:06,898 --> 00:37:08,234
Let's get out of here.

617
00:37:08,354 --> 00:37:09,866
Just hold on a second.

618
00:37:11,871 --> 00:37:15,709
As I was walking past my son's bedroom
while he was sleeping,

619
00:37:16,766 --> 00:37:17,821
it hit me.

620
00:37:18,949 --> 00:37:20,652
It's like, "what about him?

621
00:37:20,772 --> 00:37:24,802
"i mean, do you want him to grow up
without a father like you did?"

622
00:37:26,256 --> 00:37:27,915
That straightened me out.

623
00:37:28,352 --> 00:37:30,069
I've been sober ever since.

624
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:35,406
Thanks for listening
and keep coming back.

625
00:37:39,277 --> 00:37:41,376
Will you just wait for me in the car?

626
00:37:41,496 --> 00:37:43,695
I'm only gonna be a moment.

627
00:37:57,714 --> 00:38:00,522
